{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852699948,"sessionID":"ses_286ee9b3dffesjGz3k6Rl1TiT0","part":{"id":"prt_d7911bdd40013gFgOwfY3cK96Z","messageID":"msg_d7911a824001On14rRU0Q5awy2","sessionID":"ses_286ee9b3dffesjGz3k6Rl1TiT0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a88f2c5d1cae4e0592819fc5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement Valkey storage backend for the `Store` interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage keyed by session ID with expiry and last-activity indexing for garbage collection. Valkey is a Redis fork with enhanced performance and features.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The agentcube system requires a Valkey-backed storage implementation for session management as an alternative to Redis. The `Store` interface was defined in AR-012; this AR implements the Valkey provider using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`.\n12: \n13: ### Goal\n14: \n15: Implement `valkeyStore` in `pkg/store` with:\n16: - Full `Store` interface implementation\n17: - Sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking\n18: - Multi-block atomic operations\n19: - Configuration via environment variables\n20: - Optional client optimization flags\n21: \n22: ### Value\n23: - Production-ready Valkey backend for session storage\n24: - Improved performance over Redis (enhanced Redis fork)\n25: - Efficient session garbage collection via indexed queries\n26: - Atomic operations ensuring data consistency\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## Scope\n31: \n32: ### In-Scope\n33: \n34: | Deliverable | Description |\n35: |-------------|-------------|\n36: | `store_valkey.go` | Valkey store implementation |\n37: | `valkeyStore` struct | Client, key prefixes, ZSET keys |\n38: | `makeValkeyOptions` | Parse VALKEY_ADDR, VALKEY_PASSWORD, VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE, VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE |\n39: | All Store methods | Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close |\n40: \n41: ### Code Structure\n42: \n43: ```\n44: pkg/store/\n45: ├── store_valkey.go   # Valkey implementation\n46: ├── store_redis.go    # Redis implementation (AR-013)\n47: ├── store.go          # Store interface (AR-012)\n48: ├── singleton.go      # Storage() singleton (AR-012)\n49: ├── errors.go         # ErrNotFound (AR-012)\n50: └── types.go          # Store type constants (AR-012)\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ### Configuration\n54: \n55: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n56: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n57: | VALKEY_ADDR | Yes | - | Valkey server addresses (comma-separated) |\n58: | VALKEY_PASSWORD | Yes* | - | Valkey password |\n59: | VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED | No | true | Set to \"false\" to allow empty password |\n60: | VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE | No | false | Set to \"true\" to disable client-side cache |\n61: | VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE | No | false | Set to \"true\" to force single client mode |\n62: | STORE_TYPE | No | redis | Set to \"valkey\" for Valkey backend |\n63: \n64: *Required unless VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false\n65: \n66: ### Key Patterns\n67: \n68: | Key | Pattern | Type |\n69: |-----|---------|------|\n70: | Session data | `session:{sessionID}` | String (JSON) |\n71: | Expiry index | `session:expiry` | ZSET (score = ExpiresAt Unix) |\n72: | Last-activity index | `session:last_activity` | ZSET (score = activity Unix) |\n73: \n74: ### Out-of-Scope\n75: - Redis implementation (AR-013)\n76: - Valkey Cluster support\n77: - Data encryption at rest\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## Impact Analysis\n82: \n83: ### Dependencies\n84: \n85: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n86: |------------|--------|---------|\n87: | github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go | ^1.x | Valkey client |\n88: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types | local | SandboxInfo type |\n89: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | ^2.x | Logging |\n90: \n91: ### Upstream\n92: \n93: - **AR-012 Store Interface** — Interface contract to implement\n94: - **pkg/common/types** — Provides SandboxInfo struct\n95: \n96: ### Downstream Consumers\n97: \n98: 1. **Session Manager** — CRUD operations\n99: 2. **Garbage Collector** — ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes\n100: 3. **Health Checks** — Ping for connectivity\n101: \n102: ### Risks\n103: \n104: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n105: |------|----------|------------|\n106: | Valkey unavailable | High | Ping on startup, health checks |\n107: | Data inconsistency | Medium | DoMulti for atomic operations |\n108: | Password exposure | Medium | Require explicit opt-in for empty password |\n109: | Cross-slot keys | Medium | Deployment must ensure keys in same slot for MGET |\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## Alternatives Considered\n114: \n115: ### Option 1: Direct Valkey Commands (Selected)\n116: \n117: **Approach**: Use valkey-go client directly with DoMulti for atomic operations.\n118: \n119: **Pros**:\n120: - Modern Valkey client with fluent API\n121: - Built-in connection management\n122: - DoMulti support for atomic batches\n123: - Compatible with Redis protocols\n124: \n125: **Cons**:\n126: - Newer client, less battle-tested than go-redis\n127: \n128: **Decision**: Selected — native Valkey support with optimal performance.\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ### Option 2: Redis Compatibility Mode\n133: \n134: **Approach**: Use Redis client with Valkey server.\n135: \n136: **Pros**:\n137: - Mature go-redis library\n138: \n139: **Cons**:\n140: - Lose Valkey-specific optimizations\n141: - Not using native Valkey client\n142: \n143: **Decision**: Deferred — native Valkey client preferred for feature parity.\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## Implementation Plan\n148: \n149: ### Phase 1: Struct and Options\n150: - [x] Define `valkeyStore` struct with client, key prefixes\n151: - [x] Implement `makeValkeyOptions` for env var parsing\n152: - [x] Add password validation\n153: - [x] Add VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE and VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE support\n154: \n155: ### Phase 2: Core Operations\n156: - [x] Implement `Ping` — B().Ping() → expect PONG\n157: - [x] Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID` — GET session:{id}\n158: - [x] Implement `StoreSandbox` — DoMulti: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity\n159: - [x] Implement `UpdateSandbox` — SET key value XX\n160: \n161: ### Phase 3: Deletion and Updates\n162: - [x] Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` — DoMulti: DEL, ZREM both indexes\n163: - [x] Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity` — Exists verify, ZADD\n164: \n165: ### Phase 4: Listing\n166: - [x] Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes` — Zrangebyscore on expiry, then MGET\n167: - [x] Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes` — Zrangebyscore on last_activity, then MGET\n168: - [x] Handle orphan ZSET entries gracefully in loadSandboxesBySessionIDs\n169: \n170: ### Phase 5: Lifecycle\n171: - [x] Implement `Close` — cli.Close()\n172: \n173: ### Phase 6: Testing\n174: - [ ] Unit tests for each method\n175: - [ ] Test key construction\n176: - [ ] Test error cases (not found, nil input, validation)\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Acceptance Criteria\n181: \n182: - [x] `valkeyStore` implements full `Store` interface\n183: - [x] `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` correctly configure client\n184: - [x] Password required unless VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false\n185: - [x] VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE parsed and applied when \"true\"\n186: - [x] VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE parsed and applied when \"true\"\n187: - [x] Session key format: `session:{id}`\n188: - [x] Expiry index: ZSET with score = ExpiresAt.Unix()\n189: - [x] Last-activity index: ZSET with score = time.Now().Unix() on store\n190: - [x] StoreSandbox uses atomic DoMulti\n191: - [x] UpdateSandbox requires existing key (XX flag)\n192: - [x] DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from all indexes\n193: - [x] ListExpiredSandboxes queries by expiry time\n194: - [x] ListInactiveSandboxes queries by last activity\n195: - [x] Missing session returns ErrNotFound\n196: - [x] Nil sandbox rejected with error\n197: - [x] Empty session ID rejected on UpdateSessionLastActivity\n198: - [x] Close properly terminates connection\n199: - [x] Valkey nil response correctly mapped to ErrNotFound\n\n(End of file - total 199 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement Valkey storage backend for the `Store` interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage keyed by session ID with expiry and last-activity indexing for garbage collection. Valkey is a Redis fork with enhanced performance and features.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe agentcube system requires a Valkey-backed storage implementation for session management as an alternative to Redis. The `Store` interface was defined in AR-012; this AR implements the Valkey provider using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement `valkeyStore` in `pkg/store` with:\n- Full `Store` interface implementation\n- Sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking\n- Multi-block atomic operations\n- Configuration via environment variables\n- Optional client optimization flags","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775852699933,"end":1775852699946}}}}
